(40, 10, 28, 66, 2, 10, 10, 'fear not them which kill the body', 'Fear and Faithfulness in Trials', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not fearing those who can harm the body. Instead, they encourage a focus on faithfulness to God, who holds authority over both soul and body.', 'theme', 0.5449999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 28, 59, 4, 12, 12, 'able to destroy both soul and body', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of God over life and death. Matthew highlights God''s power to destroy both soul and body, while James refers to God as the lawgiver who can save and destroy.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
